### Common Commands
```bash
# Development
npm run dev                    # Start all development servers
npm run dev:api               # Start Hono.js API locally
npm run dev:dashboard         # Start Next.js dashboard
npm run dev:extension         # Watch extension files

# Database
npm run db:migrate            # Run Turso migrations
npm run db:seed              # Seed with LFA business data
npm run db:studio            # Open Drizzle Studio

# Testing
npm run test                 # Run all tests
npm run test:extension       # Test extension code
npm run test:api            # Test API endpoints

# Deployment
npm run build:extension      # Build for Chrome Web Store
npm run deploy:api          # Deploy to Cloudflare Workers
npm run deploy:dashboard    # Deploy to Cloudflare Pages
```

### Critical Requirements
- **Google Maps Compatibility**: Handle frequent DOM structure changes gracefully
- **Performance**: No noticeable impact on Maps loading or interaction
- **Reliability**: Extension must work even when API is unavailable
- **Privacy**: Minimal data collection, anonymous analytics only
- **Scalability**: Design for thousands of concurrent users on free Cloudflare tier

Remember: Focus on seamless local business discovery. The technical architecture should make it effortless for users to find and support Local First Arizona member businesses during their natural search behavior.